WEBVTT

00:06.306 --> 00:09.977 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Good evening.
I'm Hari Sreenivasan. Gwen Ifill
and Judy Woodruff are away.

00:09.977 --> 00:14.214 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:
Britain's prime minister says a
bomb is a possible cause in

00:14.214 --> 00:20.487 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the mysterious plane crash above
Sinai, but Russia and Egypt deny
those claims.

00:20.487 --> 00:25.259 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Also ahead: inside America's
nuclear arsenal. We take a look
at it's newest $8 billion
upgrade.

00:25.259 --> 00:29.763 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAJ. GEN. GARRETT HARENCAK, U.S.
Air Force: We're bringing this
weapon to the 21st century.

00:29.763 --> 00:35.869 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We're bringing it to 2015. We
are updating its components.
We're making it safer, more

00:35.869 --> 00:38.272 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
secure, and we're making
it more effective.

00:38.272 --> 00:42.910 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Plus, George
H.W. Bush reveals what he really
thinks about Dick Cheney and

00:42.910 --> 00:47.281 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Donald Rumsfeld in Jon Meacham's
new biography on the former
president.

00:47.281 --> 00:48.548 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JON MEACHAM, Author, "Destiny
and Power: The American Odyssey
of George Herbert Walker

00:48.548 --> 00:53.854 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Bush": George H.W. Bush said
that he believed that Cheney was
responsible for a good bit

00:53.854 --> 01:00.027 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of that hawkish image and that
he wished that Cheney had not
had as much influence, that

01:00.027 --> 01:02.663 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
he -- that Dick Cheney should
have had his -- quote -- "own
State Department."

01:02.663 --> 01:04.898 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: All that and
more on tonight's "PBS
NewsHour."

01:04.898 --> 01:10.804 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:10.804 --> 01:23.216 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The crash of a
Russian jetliner in Egypt
morphed into an international
dispute

01:23.216 --> 01:28.121 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
today on whether a bomb was
behind it. All 224 people on
board were killed when the plane

01:28.121 --> 01:32.793 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
broke up Saturday, just 23
minutes after taking of from
Sharm el-Sheikh.

01:32.793 --> 01:37.764 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now the leaders of Britain,
Russia and Egypt are openly
disagreeing about the cause.

01:37.764 --> 01:42.436 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID CAMERON, British Prime
Minister: We cannot be certain
that the Russian airliner

01:42.436 --> 01:46.039 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was brought down by a terrorist
bomb. But it looks increasingly
likely that that was

01:46.039 --> 01:48.041 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the case.

01:48.041 --> 01:51.979 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: British Prime
Minister David Cameron spent the
day defending his decision

01:51.979 --> 01:57.751 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to stop all British flights to
and from Sharm el-Sheikh in
Egypt, pending the crash
investigation.

01:57.751 --> 02:02.122 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID CAMERON: The reason we
have acted before that is
because of the intelligence and
information

02:02.122 --> 02:07.761 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
we had that gave us the concern
that it was more likely than not
it was a terrorist bomb.

02:07.761 --> 02:11.765 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Russian
officials insisted any talk that
a bomb destroyed the Metrojet

02:11.765 --> 02:16.103 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
airliner is just speculation.
And the Russian Foreign Ministry
urged Britain to share any

02:16.103 --> 02:18.538 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
intelligence it has.

02:18.538 --> 02:21.274 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARIA ZAKHAROVA, Russian Foreign
Ministry (through translator):
Honestly, what's really

02:21.274 --> 02:25.712 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
shocking is the realization that
the British government has some
kind of information that

02:25.712 --> 02:30.617 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
could shed light on what
happened in the skies above
Egypt. That information, if it
exists,

02:30.617 --> 02:34.021 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and judging by the fact that the
head of the Foreign Office
pronounced it does exist, that

02:34.021 --> 02:37.157 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
information was never shared
with the Russian side.

02:37.157 --> 02:40.660 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The Kremlin
said President Vladimir Putin
raised those concerns in a

02:40.660 --> 02:45.232 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
phone call with Prime Minister
Cameron. Meanwhile, Egypt's
government maintained the crash
of

02:45.232 --> 02:49.936 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the Russian jet -- quote --
"wasn't a terror act." And under
a new law, news organizations

02:49.936 --> 02:55.909 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
there that report anything to
contrary could face hefty fines.

02:55.909 --> 03:00.714 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Egyptian president, Abdel
Fattah El-Sisi, was in London
today to meet with Cameron.

03:00.714 --> 03:05.285 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
El-Sisi has warned against
expecting much from the
investigation anytime soon. But
he

03:05.285 --> 03:08.422 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
said British security teams
checked Sharm el-Sheikh's
airport 10 months ago and would

03:08.422 --> 03:11.425 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
be welcome to do so again.

03:11.425 --> 03:14.761 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ABDEL FATTAH EL-SISI, Egyptian
President (through translator):
I understand that the prime
minister

03:14.761 --> 03:19.099 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
wants to be assured of his
citizens' well-being. This is
his right. We're prepared to
cooperate

03:19.099 --> 03:23.737 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
further with any procedures that
reassure all our friends that
the security measures

03:23.737 --> 03:28.775 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in place at Sharm el-Sheikh
airport are enough and that the
airport is safe to a good
standard.

03:28.775 --> 03:33.747 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Stepped-up
security screenings were in
evidence at the Red Sea resort's
airport

03:33.747 --> 03:38.218 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
today. Thousands of tourists
remained stranded there, after
Ireland, Germany and the
Netherlands

03:38.218 --> 03:43.723 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
followed Britain's lead and also
suspended their flights. Later,
British carriers Monarch

03:43.723 --> 03:48.795 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and EasyJet announced they will
begin evacuation flights to
Sharm el-Sheikh tomorrow with
official

03:48.795 --> 03:54.868 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
approval to bring the
vacationers home. That process
could take up to 10 days.

03:54.868 --> 03:58.772 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In Washington, President Obama
said U.S. officials are taking
-- quote -- "very seriously" the

03:58.772 --> 04:02.642 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
possibility that a bomb
destroyed the Russian plane.

04:02.642 --> 04:08.615 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The death toll from a factory
collapse in Pakistan rose to at
least 20 today. Some 200

04:08.615 --> 04:13.420 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
workers were believed to be
inside the four-story building
when it gave way overnight in
Lahore.

04:13.420 --> 04:16.990 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Rescuers painstakingly searched
the rubble for signs of
survivors and used heavy
machinery

04:16.990 --> 04:21.661 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to clear debris. Some of those
trapped used cell phones to call
for help.

04:21.661 --> 04:26.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So far, 102 people have been
pulled out alive. Survivors say
cracks had appeared in the walls

04:26.500 --> 04:30.470 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
after a powerful
earthquake last week.

04:30.470 --> 04:35.275 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The European Union made a
striking forecast today, that
another three million migrants

04:35.275 --> 04:40.614 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
could arrive next year. That
came as an estimated 25,000
people waited on Lesbos and
other Greek

04:40.614 --> 04:44.751 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
islands, hoping a ferry
strike there will end.

04:44.751 --> 04:48.488 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Lindsey Hilsum of Independent
Television News filed this
report from Lesbos.

04:48.488 --> 04:52.859 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LINDSEY HILSUM: The Greek prime
minister and the president of
the European Parliament landed

04:52.859 --> 04:58.198 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in Lesbos this morning and were
immediately confronted with the
reality of the situation.

04:58.198 --> 05:04.037 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARTIN SCHULZ, President,
European Parliament (through
translator): Just as we were
arriving

05:04.037 --> 05:08.208 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
here with Mr. Tsipras, we saw
boats coming across the sea.
People were jumping into the

05:08.208 --> 05:13.413 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
water and swimming to the beach.
We're truly facing a dramatic
situation here.

05:13.413 --> 05:18.084 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LINDSEY HILSUM: They went to see
a so-called hot spot, where new
arrivals are supposed

05:18.084 --> 05:22.722 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to be registered and sent on to
other wealthier E.U. countries.

05:22.722 --> 05:26.326 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ALEXIS TSIPRAS, Greek Prime
Minister: The key issue is to
not encourage these people

05:26.326 --> 05:34.568 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
take the boat of death and to
take the risk to lose their
lives in the Aegean Sea. And

05:34.568 --> 05:43.210 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the only way is to give the hope
that someday they will have the
chance to be in this mechanism

05:43.210 --> 05:46.913 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
for resettlement directly from
the Turkish coast to Europe.

05:46.913 --> 05:53.920 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LINDSEY HILSUM: Just a few yards
from the airport, we met the
Omira family from Damascus.

05:53.920 --> 05:59.859 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Sitting on the rocks in the
sunshine, they looked as if they
might be on holiday; 77-year-old

05:59.859 --> 06:06.399 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Omar is getting pretty
good at skimming stones.

06:06.399 --> 06:10.070 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Hard to imagine what they were
going through night before last,
as a people smuggler crammed

06:10.070 --> 06:12.839 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
them into a boat on
the Turkish coast.

06:12.839 --> 06:19.412 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AMER OMIRA, Refugee: He told us
30 people only, then maybe 50
people, 70 people, I don't

06:19.412 --> 06:20.680 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
know.

06:20.680 --> 06:24.484 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
LINDSEY HILSUM: So you
were really crowded?

06:24.484 --> 06:31.124 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AMER OMIRA: Yes, yes, yes. We
told us -- no, it's very, very
dangerous. Then he brought

06:31.124 --> 06:36.696 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the gun, and pow, pow. If you
don't believe me, we will -- a
gun.

06:36.696 --> 06:39.299 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
LINDSEY HILSUM: So he
threatened to shoot you?

06:39.299 --> 06:41.568 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
AMER OMIRA: Yes, yes.

06:41.568 --> 06:45.839 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LINDSEY HILSUM: Around the port,
we found hundreds of people
stranded because the ferry

06:45.839 --> 06:50.443 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
operators have been on strike
since Monday, so there's no way
to get to Athens.

06:50.443 --> 06:56.683 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They sleep in tents or on the
streets. The people here are
hoping to get on the ferry

06:56.683 --> 07:01.988 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to Athens tomorrow, when the
strike is over, but that's not
going to be an end to the
problem;

07:01.988 --> 07:08.795 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
5,000 or 6,000 refugees and
migrants are turning up on the
Greek islands every day still,
100,000

07:08.795 --> 07:12.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
here in Lesbos just in
the last three weeks.

07:12.866 --> 07:18.938 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In the background, Lesbos' own
Statue of Liberty, the brain
child of a local man who went to

07:18.938 --> 07:25.345 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
New York years ago. He can't
imagine that, 85 years on, the
huddled masses would come

07:25.345 --> 07:28.114 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to his home island.

07:28.114 --> 07:31.551 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The United
Nations warned today that even
rough winter seas are not

07:31.551 --> 07:36.056 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
likely to stop the waves of
migrants trying to reach Greece.

07:36.056 --> 07:42.095 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The U.S. House overwhelmingly
approved a $325 billion highway
bill today. It maintains current

07:42.095 --> 07:47.934 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
levels of spending over six
years, amid concerns that aging
roads and bridges will need more

07:47.934 --> 07:52.372 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
funding. It also includes a
provision to reauthorize the
Export-Import Bank. The House
version

07:52.372 --> 07:55.942 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
must be reconciled with the
Senate's highway bill.

07:55.942 --> 08:01.648 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The U.S. and 11 other countries
released the text of a sweeping
Pacific Rim trade deal

08:01.648 --> 08:05.985 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
today, setting up a fight in
Congress. The Trans-Pacific
Partnership was negotiated for

08:05.985 --> 08:11.291 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
more than five years. The White
House says its eliminates some
18,000 taxes that other

08:11.291 --> 08:15.061 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
countries impose on U.S.
exports. It also contains
provisions to discourage forced
labor

08:15.061 --> 08:18.198 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and provide rights
to workers overseas.

08:18.198 --> 08:21.768 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
At the U.S. Capitol, the new
House speaker, Paul Ryan, said
lawmakers need time to digest

08:21.768 --> 08:24.003 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the thousands of pages.

08:24.003 --> 08:26.639 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
REP. PAUL RYAN (R-WI), Speaker
of the House: I'm pleased with
the process we have coming

08:26.639 --> 08:32.379 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
before us, open, transparent.
People get to see it, members of
Congress get to see it,

08:32.379 --> 08:36.316 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
and then we will decided
independently after consulting
with our constituents and our
conscience

08:36.316 --> 08:39.386 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
what our position on anything
like a trade agreement will be.

08:39.386 --> 08:41.388 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: On the
Democratic side, presidential
hopeful Hillary Clinton and
others

08:41.388 --> 08:44.958 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
have already come out
against the deal.

08:44.958 --> 08:49.462 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The reform Jewish movement in
the U.S. passed a far-reaching
resolution today in support

08:49.462 --> 08:54.567 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of transgender rights. Meeting
in Orlando, members of the Union
for Reform Judaism voted

08:54.567 --> 09:00.840 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for gender-neutral language and
bathrooms in their
congregations. The group has 1.5

09:00.840 --> 09:04.778 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
million members. Other religious
bodies, including the Episcopal
Church and the United Church

09:04.778 --> 09:09.682 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
of Christ, have approved
transgender resolutions, but
none has gone as far as this
one.

09:09.682 --> 09:13.686 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
