the growing trend.

36:41.232 --> 36:44.669 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RICHARD GREENWALD, Brooklyn
College: More and more companies
are hiring freelancers.

36:44.669 --> 36:47.038 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Right now, we have 40 percent of
the work force working
contingently, without any safety

36:47.038 --> 36:48.973 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
net.

36:48.973 --> 36:53.545 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: Greenwald is a
historian of the workplace and
has been studying the new
economy

36:53.545 --> 36:58.683 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
for an upcoming book
called "The Death of 9-5."

36:58.683 --> 37:02.754 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Almost half of all current
American workers, he has
discovered, now get the bulk of
their

37:02.754 --> 37:06.491 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
