37:25.777 --> 37:30.849 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: But to Greenwald,
the insecurity of contingent
work without benefits isn't

37:30.849 --> 37:37.122 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
normal at all. The premise of
WeWork, however, is that if
outsourcing is inexorable, at
least

37:37.122 --> 37:42.594 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the outsourced have a cool and
convenient place to set up shop.

37:42.594 --> 37:46.297 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Anastasia Morozova does
marketing for a start-up real
estate firm. Why doesn't she
telecommute

37:46.297 --> 37:49.601 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
for free from home
or at Starbucks?

37:49.601 --> 37:52.470 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ANASTASIA MOROZOVA, Curzon Real
Estate: Too many distractions.
One could say that there

37:52.470 --> 37:56.674 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
