hawkishness. He didn't like the
-- he didn't like the axis

47:40.858 --> 47:43.127 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
of evil.

47:43.127 --> 47:46.063 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JON MEACHAM: Right. He said,
"Historically, I don't think
that will be -- will benefit

47:46.063 --> 47:48.599 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
anything."

47:48.599 --> 47:53.437 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He didn't like the swaggering
rhetoric of his son's
administration.

47:53.437 --> 47:55.706 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And then
the Dick Cheney...

47:55.706 --> 47:57.475 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JON MEACHAM: Right.

47:57.475 --> 48:02.913 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: You know, who he
-- turns out he felt was -- had
too much influence in his

48:02.913 --> 48:05.182 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
son's administration.

48:05.182 --> 48:10.688 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JON MEACHAM: George H.W. Bush
said that he believed that
Cheney was responsible for a

48:10.688 --> 48:17.461 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
good bit of that hawkish image,
and that he wished that Cheney
had not had as much influence,

48:17.461 --> 48:21.198 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that he -- that Dick Cheney
should have had his -- quote --
"own State Department," and

48:21.198 --> 48:24.135 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
that vice presidents
shouldn't do that.

48:24.135 --> 48:29.006 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
When I took that to Vice
President Cheney, he read it and
said, "Fascinating."

48:29.006 --> 48:36.180 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But when you took
it to President Bush 43, George
W. Bush, what did he say?

48:36.180 --> 48:40.351 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JON MEACHAM: Well, he said that
he had never -- his father had
never said that to him.

48:40.351 --> 48:44.155 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He said it would have been out
of character for his father to
say, "Hey, you have got

48:44.155 --> 48:48.425 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to rein in Cheney, he's ruining
your administration, that that
conversation never took place.

48:48.425 --> 48:52.396 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: He was publicly
supportive of going into Iraq,
the decision to invade

48:52.396 --> 48:56.967 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Iraq in 2003, but he clearly
had misgivings about it.

48:56.967 --> 49:01.438 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JON MEACHAM: He had what a
friend called anxieties. He was
anxious about it.

49:01.438 --> 49:06.944 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He also privately wrote his son
a note, saying that if the man
won't comply, meaning Saddam,

49:06.944 --> 49:12.516 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
then you have to do what you
have to do. And one of the
things about that I think
historically

49:12.516 --> 49:19.456 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is important is, George H.W.
Bush had his own war with
Saddam, in which he was quite

49:19.456 --> 49:24.028 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
unilateral. He was willing --
one of the things that emerges
in the president's diary is
that,

49:24.028 --> 49:27.598 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
on five or six different
occasions, he talks about how he
would be willing to be
impeached,

49:27.598 --> 49:32.703 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that, even if the Congress said
in 1990-'91, we're not
authorizing the use of force, he

49:32.703 --> 49:35.472 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
was willing to go.

49:35.472 --> 49:39.243 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the first Bush to talk about
Saddam in terms of good vs. evil
wasn't George W. Bush...

49:39.243 --> 49:39.844 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Right.

49:39.844 --> 49:40.911 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JON MEACHAM: ... but Bush 41.

49:40.911 --> 49:42.346 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Was -- was
this -- was the father.

49:42.346 --> 49:44.048 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JON MEACHAM: Right.

49:44.048 --> 49:47.051 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And yet he went
on to have, as you said,
anxieties about what his son

49:47.051 --> 49:49.720 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
did after 9/11.

49:49.720 --> 49:54.225 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JON MEACHAM: One of the key
things about Bush 41 is the
sense of deference to whomever
the

49:54.225 --> 49:57.862 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
president happens to
be at a given moment.

49:57.862 --> 50:01.799 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He believed that his son was
confronting something that no
president since Lincoln had
done,

50:01.799 --> 50:05.002 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
which was warfare
on American soil.

50:05.002 --> 50:08.672 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And you have
talked to him a lot since he
left office, which was, what,

50:08.672 --> 50:09.940 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
23 years ago.

50:09.940 --> 50:11.876 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JON MEACHAM: Yes.

50:11.876 --> 50:16.247 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What does he say
about the hyper-partisanship in
Washington now?

50:16.247 --> 50:21.518 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JON MEACHAM: It worries him
enormously, because he -- and he
saw it happen as he was
governing.

50:21.518 --> 50:24.455 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It happened right around him.

50:24.455 --> 50:29.593 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, the rise of Gingrich,
the rise of freelance
partisanship happened when he
was

50:29.593 --> 50:32.863 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
willing to take the political
heat, break the "Read my lips"
pledge, do what he thought

50:32.863 --> 50:35.065 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
was best for the country.

50:35.065 --> 50:41.205 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's one of the key things
about George Bush, is, no matter
how you feel about how

50:41.205 --> 50:46.210 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
