tough campaigner -- in fact, he
talks in his diary about, "I'm

50:46.210 --> 50:50.881 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
stronger, I'm tougher. If I had
kept letting the press define me
as a wimp or a loser,

50:50.881 --> 50:55.586 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I wouldn't be here,
almost winning in 1988."

50:55.586 --> 51:03.961 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But once he was in office, he
tried to put the country first,
and he acted against his

51:03.961 --> 51:09.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
own political interest. The
great example is the 1990 budget
deal. He had run against

51:09.667 --> 51:14.405 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
raising taxes. He got into it.
He saw he needed to, so he did
that. And he knew at the time

51:14.405 --> 51:16.607 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
that it could cost
him reelection.

51:16.607 --> 51:21.545 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: You said to me,
just finally, a moment ago this
may be the last time a president

51:21.545 --> 51:24.915 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
gives this kind of access while
he or she is still alive.

51:24.915 --> 51:27.885 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JON MEACHAM: It's possible.

51:27.885 --> 51:35.259 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's -- these kind of diaries
are unique. He kept audio
diaries throughout his --
episodically

51:35.259 --> 51:39.863 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as vice president, and then
fairly regularly as president.
There are all sorts of legal

51:39.863 --> 51:44.535 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
issues with that and
who listens to them.

51:44.535 --> 51:50.507 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But this is as close as many of
us, I think, are going to get to
actually sitting in the

51:50.507 --> 51:58.015 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Oval Office. This is him talking
at moments of great triumph, at
moments of tragedy. It's

51:58.015 --> 52:04.722 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
a remarkable historical
document, his presidential
diary, because it's as high
politics really

52:04.722 --> 52:09.093 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
is, but we so rarely get
to see. And, here, we do.

52:09.093 --> 52:13.230 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The book is
"Destiny and Power: The American
Odyssey of George Herbert Walker

52:13.230 --> 52:14.631 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Bush,"

52:14.631 --> 52:19.336 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Jon Meacham, thank you
for bringing it to us.

52:19.336 --> 52:30.147 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
